# tcc

> A tiny C compiler that can run C source files as scripts and otherwise has command line options similar to `gcc`
> See also: gcc
> More information: https://bellard.org/tcc/tcc-doc.html

- Compile and link specific files to generate an executable:

`tcc -o {string executable} {/?file+ C source file}`

- Run a specific file and pass arguments to it:

`tcc -run {/?file C source file} {any* argument}`
